  "solution": "The radiative transfer equation is given by \\(\\frac{dI_\\nu}{ds} = -\\alpha_\\nu I_\\nu + j_\\nu\\). With the initial condition \\(I_\\nu(0) = 8.256 \\times 10^{-7} \\, \\mathrm{W\\,m^{-2}\\,sr^{-1}\\,Hz^{-1}}\\), the solution after a path length \\(s = ds\\) is \\(I_\\nu(s) = I_\\nu(0) e^{-\\tau_\\nu} + \\frac{j_\\nu}{\\alpha_\\nu} (1 - e^{-\\tau_\\nu})\\), where \\(\\tau_\\nu = \\alpha_\\nu s\\) is the optical depth. Given parameters: \\(\\alpha_\\nu = 1.724 \\times 10^{-22} \\, \\mathrm{m^{-1}}\\), \\(j_\\nu = 6.245 \\times 10^{-15} \\, \\mathrm{W\\,m^{-3}\\,sr^{-1}\\,Hz^{-1}}\\), \\(ds = 4.969 \\times 10^{17} \\, \\mathrm{m}\\). Compute \\(\\tau_\\nu = \\alpha_\\nu \\times ds = (1.724 \\times 10^{-22}) \\times (4.969 \\times 10^{17}) = 8.566556 \\times 10^{-5}\\). Since \\(\\tau_\\nu\\) is small, \\(e^{-\\tau_\\nu} \\approx 1 - \\tau_\\nu = 0.99991433444\\). Compute \\(\\frac{j_\\nu}{\\alpha_\\nu} = \\frac{6.245 \\times 10^{-15}}{1.724 \\times 10^{-22}} = 3.62267905 \\times 10^{7} \\, \\mathrm{W\\,m^{-2}\\,sr^{-1}\\,Hz^{-1}}\\). Then, \\(I_\\nu(s) = (8.256 \\times 10^{-7}) \\times 0.99991433444 + (3.62267905 \\times 10^{7}) \\times (8.566556 \\times 10^{-5}) = 8.255292745 \\times 10^{-7} + 3103.388274 = 3103.388274 \\, \\mathrm{W\\,m^{-2}\\,sr^{-1}\\,Hz^{-1}}\\). Rounding to four significant figures gives the final result.",
  "final answer": "3.103 × 10^3 W m^{-2} sr^{-1} Hz^{-1}"
}

